---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const seo = {"title": "Teeth Whitening | D‑Essence Wellness", "description": "Brighter smiles with minimized sensitivity protocols.", "canonical": "/services/teeth-whitening", "type": "website", "ogImage": "/og-default" };
---

<BaseLayout {...seo}>

<section class="relative isolate paper">

<style is:global>
  :root{
    --paper:#F8F6F2; --ink:#141414; --muted:#5a5a5a; --rule:#E6E1D8;
  }
  .paper{ background:var(--paper); color:var(--ink); }
  .rule{ border-color:var(--rule); }
  .muted{ color:var(--muted); }
  .measure{ max-width: 64ch; }
  .dropcap:first-letter{ float:left; font-size:3.2rem; line-height:1; padding-right:.35rem; padding-top:.2rem; font-weight:600; }
  .ataglance{ display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:.75rem 1.25rem; font-size:.95rem; color:var(--muted); }
  .ataglance span::after{ content:"·"; margin-left:1.25rem; color:var(--muted); }
  .ataglance span:last-child::after{ content:""; margin:0; }
  .pullquote{ border-left:2px solid var(--ink); padding-left:.85rem; font-style:italic; color:#3b3b3b; margin: 1.25rem 0; }
  @media (max-width: 1023px){ .side-col{ display:none; } }
  details.faq summary{ list-style:none; }
  details.faq summary::-webkit-details-marker{ display:none; }
  .faq-toggle{ width:1.1rem; height:1.1rem; margin-right:.5rem; flex:0 0 auto; }
  details.faq[open] .plus{ display:none; }
  details.faq:not([open]) .minus{ display:none; }
  .icon-check{ width:1.1rem; height:1.1rem; flex:0 0 auto; margin-top:.15rem;}
  .timeline{ position:relative; }
  .timeline::before{ content:""; position:absolute; left:.9rem; top:.25rem; bottom:.25rem; width:2px; background:var(--rule); }
  .tl-step{ position:relative; padding-left:2.25rem; }
  .tl-badge{ position:absolute; left:0; top:.1rem; width:1.8rem; height:1.8rem; border-radius:999px; background:var(--ink); color:#fff; font-size:.9rem; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-weight:600; }
  .tl-title{ font-weight:600; }
</style>

  <!-- HERO (left‑aligned, no breadcrumb) -->
  <div class="px-6 pt-28 md:pt-32 pb-10">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
      <div class="service-head">
  <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
    <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border rule px-3 py-1 text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.18em] opacity-80">Service</span>
  </div>
  <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl md:text-6xl font-semibold leading-tight tracking-tight">Teeth Whitening</h1>
  <p class="mt-4 text-lg md:text-xl muted measure">Brighter smiles with minimized sensitivity protocols.</p>
<div class="mt-6 border-t rule"></div>
  <div class="mt-6 border-t rule"></div>
</div>

      <div class="mt-6 h-px w-full border-t rule"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- BODY -->
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 pb-24 grid grid-cols-12 gap-8">

    <!-- Removed left side labels entirely -->

    <!-- Main narrative -->
    <article class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-8 xl:col-span-7">
      <!-- DESCRIPTION (unique, professional) -->
      <section id="description" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Description</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 muted dropcap">Only natural enamel whitens; crowns, veneers, and tooth‑colored fillings will not change shade. Your clinician will assess your oral health, discuss goals, and recommend the safest, most effective approach for your smile and skin tone.</p>
        <p class="mt-3 muted">
          It works by temporarily blocking nerve signals to specific muscles, softening lines such as frown lines, forehead creases, and crow’s feet.
          Results develop within a few days and last around 3–4 months, leaving the skin smoother and the appearance refreshed while maintaining natural expressions.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 ataglance"><span>Dentist‑supervised</span><span>Fast or gradual options</span><span>Enamel‑safe gels</span><span>Natural teeth only</span></div>
        <p class="pullquote">“Brighter teeth with clinically proven, peroxide‑based gels—tailored to your smile.”
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- BENEFITS (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="benefits" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Benefits</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-10 gap-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Clinically proven whitening with dentist‑selected peroxide gels.</div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Fast in‑office results or gradual, even whitening with custom trays.</div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Customized to your enamel, sensitivity level, and starting shade.</div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Safer application with gum protection and professional oversight.</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- THE PROCESS (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="process" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">The Process</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 timeline space-y-6">
          <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-badge">1</div><p class="tl-title">Consultation</p><p class="muted mt-1">Assessment of goals and medical history, mapping injection points and confirming candidacy.</p></div>
          <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-badge">2</div><p class="tl-title">Treatment</p><p class="muted mt-1">Small injections with a fine needle into targeted muscles; procedure usually takes 10–15 minutes.</p></div>
          <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-badge">3</div><p class="tl-title">Follow‑Up</p><p class="muted mt-1">Results develop in 3–5 days with full effect at 2 weeks. Effects last about 3–4 months.</p></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- PRE / POST (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="care" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Pre and Post‑Treatment Instructions</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
          <div><p class="font-medium">Before your visit</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 muted mt-2 space-y-2"><li>Schedule a recent dental cleaning; treat active decay or gum issues before whitening.</li><li>Use a desensitizing toothpaste daily for 1–2 weeks prior if you are prone to sensitivity.</li><li>Avoid strongly staining foods/drinks and tobacco for 24–48 hours before the appointment.</li><li>Arrive with clean teeth; do not use whitening strips for several days beforehand unless advised.</li></ul>
          </div>
          <div><p class="font-medium">After your visit</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 muted mt-2 space-y-2"><li>Avoid coffee, tea, red wine, dark sauces, and tobacco for 24–48 hours; brush after meals and use SPF lip balm.</li><li>If sensitivity occurs, use a potassium‑nitrate or fluoride toothpaste/gel; avoid very hot/cold foods temporarily.</li><li>Resume normal brushing and flossing; avoid harsh whitening products unless directed by your dentist.</li><li>For take‑home trays, follow wear time and gel amount exactly as instructed; store gels as labeled.</li></ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- FAQs (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="faqs" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer">Is professional whitening safe?</summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Yes—when supervised by a dental professional. Peroxide‑based gels lighten stains while protective measures help safeguard gums and enamel.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer">In‑office or take‑home: which is better?</summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Both are effective. In‑office whitening is faster; custom trays whiten more gradually and can be easier to maintain. Your plan is tailored to your goals and sensitivity.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer">How many shades whiter will I get—and how long will it last?</summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Results vary by starting shade and stain type. Many patients see noticeable improvement after one in‑office visit or a 1–2 week tray course. With good habits, results can last months to years; occasional touch‑ups help.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer">Will it whiten crowns, veneers, or fillings?</summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">No—only natural enamel changes color. If your restorations no longer match after whitening, options can be discussed.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer">What about sensitivity?</summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Temporary tooth sensitivity is common and typically short‑lived. Desensitizing pastes and adjusted protocols can help make treatments comfortable.</p></details>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>

    <!-- Right margin notes (sticky cues) remain -->
    
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
